dct_title_s: The Balkans 1:250,000. Banja Luka, sheet Y-14. A.M.S. M506 (G.S.G.S. 4413)
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Banja Luka. Lambert conical orthomorphic projection. North Italy zone grid Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and and spot elevations. With a Serb and Croat glossary. Corrected from intelligence reports up to March 1944 Compiled and drawn by War Office, 1944. Map area is designated as Yugoslavia it is now Croatia and Bosnia and Herzegovina.
dct_publisher_sm: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1949.
